{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-03333/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-03333"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:33:33"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, tracking, pan"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["The woman looks around."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03333/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-03333","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03333/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-03333"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03333/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03333/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03333/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03333/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03333/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03333/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03333/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03333/canvas/1/ffff8f62-0778-4ed8-bce8-a4f7fa56e2de","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T14:13:56.313Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>When Alma and Reynolds first sit down at the restaurant, the camera is close to their faces and level with their eyes. The large mirror covering the wall behind Reynolds allows Alma’s reflection to be present in the frame longer than her physical body is, as the camera pans from left to right between the couple. This lengthens her time on screen and creates the illusion that Reynolds and Alma are seated closer than they actually are. However, as Cyril joins the two, the camera is situated further back in a medium shot, capturing both Reynolds and Cyril in the same frame as she takes a seat directly beside her brother. The camera then pans slowly in the opposite direction, from right to left, highlighting Alma’s physical distance from the siblings and alluding to her emotional distance. The camera comes to rest on Alma alone; Reynolds and Cyril remain together outside the frame. As she watches their dynamic from a distance, Alma is still confined to the margins of Reynolds life, despite recently being invited into the intimate space of his workshop and made his new muse.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03333/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:559.2233009708738,195.14563106796115,612.0388349514564,515.7281553398058"}}}]}]}]}